00:02:36.010 --> 00:02:40.800
But war over seeds, that’s my life’s work,
to keep seeds free, because they literally

00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:46.160
are a war over control of seeds, by a poison
cartel of three—Monsanto and Bayer, Syngenta

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:51.190
and ChemChina, Dow and DuPont—all of them
with their roots in Hitler’s Germany and

00:02:51.190 --> 00:02:53.260
finding chemicals to kill people.

00:02:53.260 --> 00:02:55.410
No wonder they’re still killing people.

00:02:55.410 --> 00:02:58.970
No wonder they’re killing our butterflies
and our bees and our pollinators.

00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:04.849
And every indicator is showing we are not
just in a severe climate catastrophe; we are

00:03:04.849 --> 00:03:06.870
in the sixth mass extinction.

00:03:06.870 --> 00:03:11.900
And both the species extinction and the climate
catastrophe are two sides of the same coin.

00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:14.140
AMY GOODMAN: Let’s start with Monsanto.

00:03:14.140 --> 00:03:20.349
Last month, India’s Supreme Court ruled
that Monsanto’s patent for Bt cotton seeds

00:03:20.349 --> 00:03:21.349
is valid.

00:03:21.349 --> 00:03:27.599
You’ve questioned if a seed is an invention
and can be patented.

00:03:27.599 --> 00:03:31.110
Talk about what Bt cotton is and why this
matters.

00:03:31.110 --> 00:03:33.209
VANDANA SHIVA: Amy, I was in the Supreme Court.

00:03:33.209 --> 00:03:35.280
I’m an intervener in that case.

00:03:35.280 --> 00:03:38.090
And Monsanto does not have a patent on Bt
cotton.

00:03:38.090 --> 00:03:42.240
And the Supreme Court did not give it a patent
on Bt cotton.

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:47.400
The only way it could have done it is by striking
down India’s law, Article 3(J) of our patent

00:03:47.400 --> 00:03:48.400
law.

00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:52.870
And I had a role with our Parliament: to shape
the amendments after the WTO trips forced

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:54.640
us to amend our laws.

00:03:54.640 --> 00:04:00.030
3(J) says plants, animals and seeds are not
human inventions, therefore they’re not

00:04:00.030 --> 00:04:03.989
patentable, because a patent is only granted
for that which is invented.

00:04:03.989 --> 00:04:05.760
So, what is the Bt cotton?

00:04:05.760 --> 00:04:12.310
There are only two kinds of GMO seeds that
account for most genetically engineered crops

00:04:12.310 --> 00:04:13.860
around the world.

00:04:13.860 --> 00:04:17.079
One is a family of crops called Bt crops,
like Bt cotton—

00:04:17.079 --> 00:04:18.910
AMY GOODMAN: What does “Bt” stand for?

00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:24.600
VANDANA SHIVA: Bacillus thuringiensis, a soil
organism which produces an endotoxin, which

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:28.219
becomes a poison only in the gut of the caterpillar
family.

00:04:28.219 --> 00:04:34.690
But in the plant, it’s a readymade toxin,
with a very broad spectrum of harm.

00:04:34.690 --> 00:04:37.940
And it’s supposed to be a pesticide-producing
plant.

00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:44.139
In fact, in the United States, it was approved
as a pesticide.

00:04:44.139 --> 00:04:48.979
As a pesticide-producing plant, every cell
of the plant is releasing a toxin at very

00:04:48.979 --> 00:04:49.979
high levels.

00:04:49.979 --> 00:04:51.680
It’s supposed to control the bollworm pest.

00:04:51.680 --> 00:04:57.210
The bollworm has become resistant, which is
in the nature of evolution.

00:04:57.210 --> 00:05:01.059
Life evolves to overcome threats.

00:05:01.059 --> 00:05:06.570
And the Bt does not—Bt cotton seed does
not have a patent, for the simple reason our

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.719
laws don’t allow it.

00:05:08.719 --> 00:05:15.770
Monsanto was illegally collecting royalties
via Indian seed companies, because they couldn’t

00:05:15.770 --> 00:05:20.330
do what they did in this country, which is
sign licensing agreements directly with the

00:05:20.330 --> 00:05:21.330
farmers.

00:05:21.330 --> 00:05:26.289
In India, they signed the licensing agreements
with the companies—with a lie that they

00:05:26.289 --> 00:05:27.960
had a patent.

00:05:27.960 --> 00:05:31.840
They signed on the U.S. patent, but India
is a sovereign country, and patent laws are

00:05:31.840 --> 00:05:34.659
sovereign laws.

00:05:34.659 --> 00:05:39.789
When they wanted to extract more royalties
and the price of seed jumped 80,000 percent,

00:05:39.789 --> 00:05:43.849
this is the main reason why the suicide belt
of India, where now 310,000 Indian farmers

00:05:43.849 --> 00:05:49.659
have committed suicide, it overlaps largely
with the cotton belt.

00:05:49.659 --> 00:05:53.909
And 99 percent of the cotton seed is controlled
by Monsanto.

00:05:53.909 --> 00:06:00.130
We have an anti-trust case in the Indian Competition
Commission saying 99 percent seed is a prima

00:06:00.130 --> 00:06:01.319
facie monopoly.

00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:06.369
Eighty thousand percent jump in seed, and
it doesn’t work to control the pests.

00:06:06.369 --> 00:06:07.520
Farmers got into debt.

00:06:07.520 --> 00:06:11.680
That’s the driver for farmer suicide.

00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:14.449
When the Indian companies said, “We can’t
keep paying.

00:06:14.449 --> 00:06:15.449
Our farmers are dying.

00:06:15.449 --> 00:06:22.610
We can’t extract more royalties,” Monsanto
sued them, using patent law, infringement.

00:06:22.610 --> 00:06:25.229
That’s when I was involved.

00:06:25.229 --> 00:06:29.830
I was called to intervene in the High Court,
and then I intervened in the Supreme Court.

00:06:29.830 --> 00:06:33.969
The attempt of Monsanto was to knock down
India’s law.

00:06:33.969 --> 00:06:35.800
They failed.

00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:40.680
Its control over media, that’s why it’s
so important to have Democracy Now!, Amy,

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:44.189
because the media is so totally in the hands
of the poison cartel.

00:06:44.189 --> 00:06:46.919
They lied about what happened in the Supreme
Court that day.

00:06:46.919 --> 00:06:47.919
AMY GOODMAN: What happened?

00:06:47.919 --> 00:06:48.919
VANDANA SHIVA: They lost.

00:06:48.919 --> 00:06:51.530
No, the Supreme Court said, “You go back
to trial.

00:06:51.530 --> 00:06:52.900
It’s between two of you.

00:06:52.900 --> 00:06:56.419
It’s not an issue of us knocking down the
law.”

00:06:56.419 --> 00:07:06.689
They wanted to declare the genetically engineered
Bt as a chemical for which they wanted a product

00:07:06.689 --> 00:07:11.930
patent, which means wherever it would have
existed, no matter where, it would have been

00:07:11.930 --> 00:07:12.930
their property.

00:07:12.930 --> 00:07:18.240
And the existence of Bt in the seed would
have been an infringement of their patent.

00:07:18.240 --> 00:07:20.020
They totally lost with their agenda.

00:07:20.020 --> 00:07:25.909
And the only way Monsanto has functioned anywhere
in the world, whether it be Brazil or Argentina

00:07:25.909 --> 00:07:28.999
or their attempt in India, is illegally.

00:07:28.999 --> 00:07:34.629
They are not just trying to shape law when
they don’t get their way.

00:07:34.629 --> 00:07:39.740
They changed the WTO system by saying, “We
are the patient, diagnostician and physician,

00:07:39.740 --> 00:07:40.749
all in one.

00:07:40.749 --> 00:07:43.759
We have to prevent farmers from saving seeds.”

00:07:43.759 --> 00:07:44.759
That’s what shaped my life.

00:07:44.759 --> 00:07:48.580
That’s why for 31 years I’ve been saving
seeds and started Navdanya.

00:07:48.580 --> 00:07:54.099
And I want to give to you, Amy, our love for
the seed, because when the suicides in the

00:07:54.099 --> 00:07:59.710
cotton belt started—’til then I was saving
crop seeds, food crop seeds—I went down

00:07:59.710 --> 00:08:02.550
and said, “I’m going to start a cotton
seed bank.”

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:03.689
Took a long time.

00:08:03.689 --> 00:08:05.989
We retrieved native cottons.

00:08:05.989 --> 00:08:07.550
We multiplied it.

00:08:07.550 --> 00:08:09.479
Farmers grow organic cotton.

00:08:09.479 --> 00:08:14.020
In the villages where the farmers are growing
organic cotton, Bt cotton has come down 60

00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:15.020
percent.

00:08:15.020 --> 00:08:16.370
And then we work with the Gandhi Ashram.

