handprinted, with indigo, which was also at

00:08:30.589 --> 00:08:31.589
one time—

00:08:31.589 --> 00:08:32.589
AMY GOODMAN: Indigo.

00:08:32.589 --> 00:08:33.589
VANDANA SHIVA: Indigo.

00:08:33.589 --> 00:08:34.589
AMY GOODMAN: The dye.

00:08:34.589 --> 00:08:35.589
VANDANA SHIVA: Dye.

00:08:35.589 --> 00:08:37.390
You know, we used to have slave conditions
for growing indigo, and Gandhi led the first

00:08:37.390 --> 00:08:41.300
satyagraha, the noncooperation, said, “We
would rather die than grow indigo.”

00:08:41.300 --> 00:08:44.450
And that’s what triggered so much of the
freedom movement.

00:08:44.450 --> 00:08:47.920
That’s with love to you for democracy, for
all life on Earth.

00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:48.920
That’s democracy.

00:08:48.920 --> 00:08:50.699
AMY GOODMAN: And this is being made by?

00:08:50.699 --> 00:08:52.160
VANDANA SHIVA: By women.

00:08:52.160 --> 00:08:53.660
AMY GOODMAN: In?

00:08:53.660 --> 00:08:56.149
VANDANA SHIVA: In central India.

00:08:56.149 --> 00:08:58.190
The central India is called Vidarbha.

00:08:58.190 --> 00:09:05.490
It is the place where Gandhi moved to create
his final ashram, to create a totally democratic

00:09:05.490 --> 00:09:06.490
society.

00:09:06.490 --> 00:09:09.430
And for him, democracy began with economic
democracy.

00:09:09.430 --> 00:09:11.360
You’ve got to produce what you need.

00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:13.490
That’s why he pulled at the spinning wheel.

00:09:13.490 --> 00:09:16.089
And for me, the seed is today’s spinning
wheel.

