00:19:23.250 --> 00:19:24.799
report two years ago.

00:19:24.799 --> 00:19:31.210
And they’re the ones who followed up the
Occupy movement’s 1 percent naming.

00:19:31.210 --> 00:19:36.919
And they constantly release annually, at the
celebration of party of the 1 percent—right

00:19:36.919 --> 00:19:42.520
now it’s a collapsing party—the Davos
meeting, where they show.

00:19:42.520 --> 00:19:52.490
Now, can you imagine, every day, $2 billion
added to the wealth of the thieves, the stealers,

00:19:52.490 --> 00:19:55.340
the casino players?

00:19:55.340 --> 00:20:00.429
And not only are they accumulating more wealth,
they’re converting the real lives of people

00:20:00.429 --> 00:20:01.650
into their wealth.

00:20:01.650 --> 00:20:06.340
My work is on seeds, to prevent seeds from
becoming the wealth of these giants.

00:20:06.340 --> 00:20:11.559
And Bill Gates has a very big role in pushing
GMOs in Africa, through the Alliance for the

00:20:11.559 --> 00:20:16.511
Green Revolution in Africa, pushing patents
on seeds, against the laws, the sovereign

00:20:16.511 --> 00:20:19.880
laws that countries like India have created.

00:20:19.880 --> 00:20:22.960
But they are privatizing water.

00:20:22.960 --> 00:20:29.130
He is part of geoengineering the extremely
false solution to the climate crisis, the

00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:30.770
melting of glaciers.

00:20:30.770 --> 00:20:36.390
And I remember in 2009 we did a study on the
third pole, on the Himalayan ecosystems, the

00:20:36.390 --> 00:20:37.890
impact on climate change.

00:20:37.890 --> 00:20:41.919
And all the pressure was put by the polluters
to say, “Deny that the glaciers are melting.

00:20:41.919 --> 00:20:42.919
Deny.”

00:20:42.919 --> 00:20:49.240
Our government flipped overnight to say, “They’re
not melting; actually, they’re increasing.”

00:20:49.240 --> 00:20:51.390
So these new reports are extremely important.

00:20:51.390 --> 00:20:56.279
And the Himalaya, Himalayan snows don’t
just support the people in the Himalaya; they

00:20:56.279 --> 00:21:01.120
support half of humanity, because all the
rivers for the most densely populated part

00:21:01.120 --> 00:21:03.700
of the world emerge from the Himalaya.

00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:06.149
And the consequences of this are huge.

00:21:06.149 --> 00:21:10.559
But the most important thing is, those women
in Ladakh, with whom I work, the Women’s

00:21:10.559 --> 00:21:18.500
Alliance, they don’t use one drop of oil
or one ounce of gas.

00:21:18.500 --> 00:21:21.240
They are totally in a renewable energy economy.

00:21:21.240 --> 00:21:22.240
And they’re being punished.

00:21:22.240 --> 00:21:27.090
That’s why climate justice is such an important
part of avoiding climate catastrophe.

00:21:27.090 --> 00:21:30.590
AMY GOODMAN: So, how does it feel to come
to the United States?

00:21:30.590 --> 00:21:34.570
Because what you’re saying, the denial of
the effects of climate change is very Trumpian.

00:21:34.570 --> 00:21:40.620
VANDANA SHIVA: Well, sadly, in that case,
it was President Obama, because he flew into

00:21:40.620 --> 00:21:46.049
Singapore to tell the governments, “Stop
pushing for legally binding emissions.”

00:21:46.049 --> 00:21:52.769
He flew into Copenhagen after having received
the Nobel Peace Prize, and called the five

00:21:52.769 --> 00:22:00.110
worst polluters—India, China included now—and
said, “Let’s get rid of the legally binding

00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:01.110
convention.”

00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:04.880
And that’s why Paris is merely an agreement.

00:22:04.880 --> 00:22:09.179
It’s not the legally binding U.N. Framework
Convention with emissions that were legally

00:22:09.179 --> 00:22:10.630
binding.

00:22:10.630 --> 00:22:15.730
And it was in the middle of the negotiations
he announced, “We’ve come to an agreement.”

00:22:15.730 --> 00:22:20.850
And that’s when Evo Morales, the president
of Bolivia, got up and said, “We were here

00:22:20.850 --> 00:22:22.830
to fight for the rights of Mother Earth.

00:22:22.830 --> 00:22:26.370
We weren’t here for the rights of polluters.

00:22:26.370 --> 00:22:29.100
And all of us are negotiating inside the hall.

00:22:29.100 --> 00:22:32.890
Five people get together and say, ’We’ve
come to an agreement to destroy the Earth.’”

00:22:32.890 --> 00:22:37.320
That’s why he worked on the rights of Mother
Earth and called many of us to become the

00:22:37.320 --> 00:22:42.530
drafting team for the draft declaration, Universal
Draft Declaration on the Rights of Mother

00:22:42.530 --> 00:22:45.000
Earth, which is available for people.

00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:50.059
And the work on the movement for the rights
of nature has grown out of that, out of the

00:22:50.059 --> 00:22:51.059
failure of Copenhagen.

00:22:51.059 --> 00:22:53.909
AMY GOODMAN: So you’re talking about 10
years ago, in 2009.

00:22:53.909 --> 00:22:55.500
VANDANA SHIVA: Ten years ago, yes.

00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:59.360
AMY GOODMAN: When President Obama flew into
Copenhagen at the U.N. climate summit.

00:22:59.360 --> 00:23:04.790
VANDANA SHIVA: Which is the tragedy these
days, that the 1 percent money machine has

00:23:04.790 --> 00:23:10.080
become so powerful that it actually controls
the political machine in a very big way.

00:23:10.080 --> 00:23:14.890
And we know the elections of the U.S. was
Facebook handing over to Cambridge Analytica

00:23:14.890 --> 00:23:20.279
the “technology” angle, and you got the
first artificial intelligence president based

00:23:20.279 --> 00:23:25.850
on algorithms of hate—hate for women, hate
for blacks, hate for Muslims, hate for migrants.

00:23:25.850 --> 00:23:30.510
Now, you can’t run democracy on the hate
machine.

00:23:30.510 --> 00:23:36.890
And you can’t run democracy by the hate
machine being fueled through the divide-and-rule

00:23:36.890 --> 00:23:42.700
policy of the 1 percent to destroy our oneness,
our solidarity, our recognition that we are

00:23:42.700 --> 00:23:48.980
one humanity and can be strong when we fight
for the rights of the planet and for our basic

00:23:48.980 --> 00:23:52.500
rights to food and water and livelihoods and
justice and democracy.

00:23:52.500 --> 00:23:58.770
AMY GOODMAN: You are famous for describing
corporate control, challenging corporate control,

00:23:58.770 --> 00:24:03.730
but then also coming up with alternative systems,
what you call food democracy.

00:24:03.730 --> 00:24:04.730
Explain.

00:24:04.730 --> 00:24:05.730
VANDANA SHIVA: Yeah.

00:24:05.730 --> 00:24:10.889
So, we’ve just done a book on biodiversity,
agroecology and regenerative organic agriculture,

00:24:10.889 --> 00:24:17.630
which is 31 years of our practice and research,
because I can’t see thinking separate from

00:24:17.630 --> 00:24:18.980
action.

00:24:18.980 --> 00:24:25.540
We find we can feed two times India’s population—two
times India’s population—by conserving

00:24:25.540 --> 00:24:30.330
biodiversity, providing more nutrition per
acre, the more biodiverse the system, and

00:24:30.330 --> 00:24:33.409
organic systems produce more nutrition.

00:24:33.409 --> 00:24:39.380
Farmers earn 10 times more by not spending
precious money on chemicals and big machines.

00:24:39.380 --> 00:24:44.450
And the Monsantos and the Bayers of the world
are imagining an agriculture without farmers,

00:24:44.450 --> 00:24:49.490
farming without farmers, farming with drones,
farming with spyware in the tractors, farming

00:24:49.490 --> 00:24:52.750
with robots, farming with artificial intelligence.

00:24:52.750 --> 00:24:56.320
They’re talking about digital agriculture
where you don’t need people.

00:24:56.320 --> 00:25:01.610
But that means no one to care for the land,
because agriculture means care for the land.

00:25:01.610 --> 00:25:06.039
We need the Green New Deal, which is such
an amazing discussion in this country.

00:25:06.039 --> 00:25:12.120
And the Green New Deal has to be to put more
people on the land, just like during the Dust

00:25:12.120 --> 00:25:14.280
Bowl in the Depression.

00:25:14.280 --> 00:25:16.580
Hands healed the Dust Bowl.

00:25:16.580 --> 00:25:19.399
We need hands to heal the planet.

00:25:19.399 --> 00:25:23.889
We have solutions to climate change, because
it’s only through taking the excess carbon

00:25:23.889 --> 00:25:29.860
and the excess nitrogen out of the air, can
we heal the broken nitrogen cycle and the

00:25:29.860 --> 00:25:31.269
carbon cycle.

00:25:31.269 --> 00:25:34.200
Ecological farming, biodiverse-intensive farming
does that.

00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:42.040
And we only need to add 2 percent, and 10
years we can solve the climate crisis.

00:25:42.040 --> 00:25:45.570
With 0.5 percent organic matter, we can get
rid of the drought.

00:25:45.570 --> 00:25:49.270
AMY GOODMAN: Explain exactly what you mean,
to the nonfarmer audience.

00:25:49.270 --> 00:25:55.530
VANDANA SHIVA: So, the basic problem of climate
change is that the planetary boundaries have

00:25:55.530 --> 00:25:56.530
been ruptured.

00:25:56.530 --> 00:26:04.159
There’s a limit of cycling of carbon, of
nitrogen and other minerals and elements.

00:26:04.159 --> 00:26:11.110
By taking fossil fuels out from underground
and burning them at a very high speed, 600

00:26:11.110 --> 00:26:15.370
million years of nature’s work—20 million
years being burned every year—we are putting

00:26:15.370 --> 00:26:19.279
too much carbon dioxide into the atmosphere,
which is why we have climate change.

00:26:19.279 --> 00:26:24.130
We use some of this fossil fuel to then make
nitrogen fertilizers, which emits a nitrous

00:26:24.130 --> 00:26:27.820
oxide, which is 300 times more deadly for
the climate.

00:26:27.820 --> 00:26:33.929
You get rid of chemicals, you get rid of fossil
fuels, and you start doing organic, all that

00:26:33.929 --> 00:26:38.840
excess carbon can be pulled back by the plants
and put back in the soil, which is why I wrote

00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:41.250
the book Soil Not Oil.

00:26:41.250 --> 00:26:46.890
When you put nitrogen-fixing plants, the pulses—you
know, everyone’s now talking of plant-based

00:26:46.890 --> 00:26:48.830
diets, proteins from plants.

00:26:48.830 --> 00:26:52.840
We did it in India forever with our lovely
dal, our pulses.

00:26:52.840 --> 00:26:54.720
They fix nitrogen nonviolently.

00:26:54.720 --> 00:26:59.860
You don’t have to blast fossil fuels at
high temperature to fix atmospheric nitrogen.

00:26:59.860 --> 00:27:04.529
The plants have the intelligence to do it,
peacefully, and give us good protein, the

00:27:04.529 --> 00:27:08.789
same way, while fixing the broken nitrogen
cycle, which if you look at the planetary

00:27:08.789 --> 00:27:14.530
boundaries graph, the nitrogen cycle is and
the biodiversity system is the most abused.

00:27:14.530 --> 00:27:19.760
And in every one of these problems, whether
it’s hunger or the chronic disease epidemic

00:27:19.760 --> 00:27:24.389
or climate change or species—you know, the
pollinators on our farm are six times more

00:27:24.389 --> 00:27:26.409
than the pollinators on the forest.

00:27:26.409 --> 00:27:34.049
And now, every year, we offer a 1-month course
on the practice of biodiversity, agroecology

00:27:34.049 --> 00:27:36.029
and organic food systems.

00:27:36.029 --> 00:27:41.440
Everywhere, the world is being healed, with
a lot of solidarity, a lot of oneness, between

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:46.400
ourselves and the web of life, and a reclaiming
of that, our intelligence.

00:27:46.400 --> 00:27:47.990
Intelligence will never be artificial.

00:27:47.990 --> 00:27:49.950
Real intelligence is what makes us live.

00:27:49.950 --> 00:27:51.880
Life is intelligence.

00:27:51.880 --> 00:27:52.880
Intelligence is democracy.

00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:58.950
AMY GOODMAN: Vandana Shiva is an Indian scholar,
environmental activist, food sovereignty and

00:27:58.950 --> 00:28:04.039
seed freedom advocate, and alternative globalization
leader and author.

00:28:04.039 --> 00:28:12.340
She’s written more than 20 books—her latest,
Oneness vs. the 1% and Who Really Feeds the

00:28:12.340 --> 00:28:13.340
World?

00:28:13.340 --> 00:28:14.340
This is Democracy Now!

00:28:14.340 --> 00:28:15.340
I’m Amy Goodman.

00:28:15.340 --> 00:28:16.309
